texts.text: For a guide about all the additions and changes in this update, see Bedrock Edition guides/Discovery Update.
The Discovery Update is the name for Minecraft: Pocket Edition version 1.1.0, a major update which was released on June 1, 2017.
The official name for the update, the Discovery Update, was revealed on March 29, 2017, in a blog post on the Minecraft website.[1]

1.2 Changes
2 Further revisions

5 References
Main articles: Pocket Edition 1.1.0 and New Nintendo 3DS Edition 1.9.19

Version exclusive Minecraft Marketplace
Woodland Mansion
Includes everything as of the Exploration Update, except for banners.
5 new blocks:
Concrete, Concrete powder, Glazed terracotta, Shulker box, and Frosted ice
7 new items:
Explorer maps, Totem of undying, Iron nugget, and 4 new spawn eggs
5 new mobs:
Llamas, vindicators, evokers, vexes and cartographer villagers
Mending and Frost Walker enchantments
6 new achievements.
Beds can be dyed in all 16 colors.

1.1.1 and 1.1.2 were released to fix various bugs.
1.1.3 added fossils, as well as various blocks to the Nether.
1.1.4 and 1.1.5 added various skin packs to the Marketplace. 1.1.5 also saw the Marketplace extracted to its own library, so that updates to the Marketplace would no longer require version upgrades.
1.1.7 was released exclusively on iOS to add support for Internet Protocol version 6.
